00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:40,120
{\an8}Oh.

2
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:49,640
{\an8}<i>The websites Rin looked up</i>
<i>were about Fire Phoenix.</i>

3
00:02:49,720 --> 00:02:51,520
{\an8}<i>Mr. Taiga's my personal designer.</i>

4
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:55,840
{\an8}Now he can come in to work
whenever he wants.

5
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:00,120
{\an8}<i>Fire Phoenix…</i>

6
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:04,280
{\an8}will pay for every life
taken from Blazing Tiger.

7
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:12,200
Mr. Taiga, would you like anything else?
I can arrange it.

8
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:17,000
I'm so happy I get to see
your face for a long time.

9
00:03:17,080 --> 00:03:20,120
Thank you very much. This is enough.

10
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:22,040
I'll have my team take over from here.

11
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:25,080
Worried I might not get it right?

12
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:28,200
You should give me some tips!

13
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:31,760
I want to have a cool style like yours.

14
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:34,240
How's the clip situation going?

15
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:37,160
Such a mood killer.

16
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:39,960
Same as always.

17
00:03:40,040 --> 00:03:43,120
Everything can be solved with money.

18
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:47,160
Right now, our legal team
is digging to see

19
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:49,280
who leaked the clip.

20
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:54,720
But it's been a long time,
and there's more than one clip.

21
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:58,960
Looks like I'll have to consult with you

22
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,640
a lot more about this place.

23
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,640
Okay.

24
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:06,880
I'm more than happy!

25
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:10,360
Always ready to help, no days off.

26
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:24,080
You okay?

27
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:28,920
Someone touch you?

28
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:32,840
Whatever.

29
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:36,680
It's a way to pass the time while waiting,
and I get to stay with you too.

30
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:40,520
Thanks a lot, Rin.

31
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:56,000
- Aru.
- Yes?

32
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:58,720
The VIP wants you to dance for him.

33
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:03,600
Dance?

34
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:06,760
- Oh, I can't dance! No way.
- Come on, just a little.

35
00:05:06,840 --> 00:05:09,200
Freestyle it. He's already tipped.

36
00:05:09,280 --> 00:05:11,440
Help out. Please.

37
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:16,200
- Where? What?
- Right here.

38
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:17,640
Just right here.

39
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:19,040
- Right here?
- Yes.

40
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:21,440
Dance right here.

41
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:28,920
Go ahead.

42
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:44,560
- A little more.
- What?

43
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:45,520
A little more!

44
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:29,840
Hey, the guy at that table
is looking at you.

45
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:41,880
Sun, come dance with me.

46
00:06:43,520 --> 00:06:46,040
No, I'll just watch you dance.

47
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:53,400
Don't you get jealous at all?

48
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:02,480
This isn't fun.

49
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:05,480
Let me sit inside.

50
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:35,360
Um…

51
00:07:35,440 --> 00:07:38,480
Pat, I'm going to the bathroom.

52
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:41,360
Hurry back, Sun.

53
00:07:42,280 --> 00:07:43,880
Hey!

54
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:45,600
I want to play pool.

55
00:07:47,960 --> 00:07:49,200
Okay, I'll be quick.

56
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:23,760
Aru, serve the VIP room.

57
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:26,760
The regular server just called in sick.

58
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:27,840
Sure!

59
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:40,400
<i>Sit here.</i>

60
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:49,760
Finish this drink first, then you can go.

61
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:53,640
Yes.

62
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:10,000
Can I go now?

63
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:13,360
Wait a bit. Stay and keep me company.

64
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:41,440
Aru.

65
00:10:42,160 --> 00:10:43,160
Aru!

66
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:54,120
Aru.

67
00:11:08,760 --> 00:11:11,040
Aru! Are you okay?

68
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:20,040
Aru, wake up!

69
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:25,080
- Sorry.
- Yes?

70
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:27,640
- Can you watch my friend for a bit?
- Sure.

71
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:28,640
Okay.

72
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:34,760
Sun, where have you been all this time?

73
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:38,240
How's your pool game, Pat?

74
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:40,920
Guess what, I pocketed a bunch of balls.

75
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,240
- Really?
- Yes.

76
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:44,040
- Well done!
- Let's keep playing.

77
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,040
Let's go.

78
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:41,280
I fired her, but Te brought her back in.

79
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:43,120
Actually, you were wrong, Nun.

80
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,680
Rin is doing her job very well.

81
00:12:45,760 --> 00:12:48,960
You don't like her, so you're trying
to push her out for no reason.

82
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:52,640
If she takes this to court,
how much would I have to pay?

83
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:54,720
You care about a few hundred thousand,

84
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:56,840
but not how I feel?

85
00:12:56,920 --> 00:12:57,760
You're going to be the boss.

86
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:01,800
Why get worked up
over a low-level employee?

87
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:05,400
You even let Taiga work in my building,

88
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:07,120
and I didn't scold you.

89
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:12,640
I agree that Rin should work here.

90
00:13:13,320 --> 00:13:15,520
Her education isn't bad.

91
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:18,800
She's a university graduate.
She can handle office work.

92
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:22,440
No more problems, right?

93
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:11,920
You can use the computer, right?

94
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:13,320
Yes.

95
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:16,920
Enter the client info from the files
and send it tomorrow.

96
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:18,520
Okay.

97
00:14:29,760 --> 00:14:32,720
Mr. Te took her back to work.

98
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:35,800
Ms. Nun said no, worried it'd get messy.

99
00:14:35,880 --> 00:14:38,840
But she depended completely on Mr. Te.

100
00:14:39,360 --> 00:14:44,080
Now what? She's gone
from security to data.

101
00:14:44,160 --> 00:14:48,920
I only knew her by her name, Rin.
Never knew her full name.

102
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:51,960
Her surname?

103
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:53,120
Yes.

104
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:01,840
Rin Sinkan.

105
00:15:03,560 --> 00:15:04,600
Can I see it?

106
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:21,880
These are the two daughters
of Inspector Phumin.

107
00:15:22,920 --> 00:15:26,560
The older one, Mew,
is a graphic designer living abroad.

108
00:15:26,640 --> 00:15:28,480
She hasn't returned since her dad passed.

109
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:34,400
The younger one is Lirin.

110
00:15:37,360 --> 00:15:38,600
She drowned.

111
00:15:48,320 --> 00:15:49,440
Over there.

112
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:51,800
That's the death certificate.

113
00:15:57,480 --> 00:15:58,720
DEATH CERTIFICATE

114
00:15:58,800 --> 00:16:00,240
LIRIN PONGRIT

115
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:02,080
STUDENT

116
00:16:03,040 --> 00:16:04,600
You don't believe

117
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:08,120
that Lirin, the inspector's youngest,
is dead, do you?

118
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:20,240
Looking good.

119
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:25,800
Thanks for keeping quiet.

120
00:16:27,840 --> 00:16:28,920
Yes.

121
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:43,640
Mr. Techut.

122
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:46,280
What happened?

123
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:47,920
Hold on.

124
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:49,480
Someone attacked me.

125
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:54,000
How did you get in here?

126
00:16:54,520 --> 00:16:56,000
I work here.

127
00:16:57,280 --> 00:16:58,360
Take me home.

128
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:00,080
Yes.

129
00:17:08,560 --> 00:17:10,599
Want me to do more to repay you?

130
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:13,599
No, sir.

131
00:17:13,680 --> 00:17:17,000
Just being able to work here
is more than enough for me.

132
00:17:17,520 --> 00:17:20,040
You're not what you seem.

133
00:17:22,319 --> 00:17:26,319
Smart, capable, and adaptable.

134
00:17:28,440 --> 00:17:29,560
Thank you.

135
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:34,880
I'm sorry for anything I did wrong before.

136
00:17:36,080 --> 00:17:39,200
Forget it. Life starts fresh every day.

137
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:44,160
You work for me now.
If Taiga does anything shady,

138
00:17:44,680 --> 00:17:48,440
tell me everything.
That guy brings trouble with him.

139
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:04,560
Here you go.

140
00:18:04,640 --> 00:18:06,160
It's 20 baht. Thank you.

141
00:18:06,240 --> 00:18:07,680
Come again.

142
00:18:12,040 --> 00:18:13,680
The order you placed, right?

143
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:15,880
Here are the two sets.

144
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:18,440
Thank you.

145
00:18:18,520 --> 00:18:20,400
Come again!

146
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:26,160
Hello.

147
00:18:27,240 --> 00:18:29,800
May I ask your name?

148
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:33,000
Sorry for the delay. I'm sorry.

149
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:13,240
I hope I won't have to bribe anyone again.

150
00:19:24,360 --> 00:19:26,280
Have you been causing trouble again?

151
00:19:27,920 --> 00:19:28,960
No.

152
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:54,680
I have high hopes for you.

153
00:19:56,520 --> 00:19:58,040
You carry my blood.

154
00:19:59,080 --> 00:20:01,520
My one true bloodline.

155
00:20:05,440 --> 00:20:06,920
What about Nun?

156
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:13,080
Remember this.

157
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:16,080
You'll be the first to have everything.

158
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:18,240
Protect 3C Corp.

159
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:20,480
It's our life, mine and yours.

160
00:21:38,520 --> 00:21:39,600
Aru.

161
00:21:43,520 --> 00:21:45,400
Hey, why are you up so early?

162
00:21:48,400 --> 00:21:51,040
Sorry, I had to move you farther.

163
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:53,320
This was the cheapest place I could find.

164
00:21:54,080 --> 00:21:56,880
It's fine. Moving in together
saves on rent.

165
00:21:57,520 --> 00:22:01,400
You're not mad, right?
I just suddenly asked you to move.

166
00:22:02,200 --> 00:22:03,160
Is something wrong?

167
00:22:08,720 --> 00:22:11,280
Nothing, I just wanted
to save up some money.

168
00:22:11,880 --> 00:22:13,320
I'll go to work now.

169
00:22:14,640 --> 00:22:15,680
Good luck!

170
00:22:15,760 --> 00:22:16,760
Okay.

171
00:22:40,240 --> 00:22:42,680
Do you have anything to request, Mr. Te?

172
00:22:42,760 --> 00:22:44,200
You can also call me to the office.

173
00:22:44,960 --> 00:22:46,520
I'm just here to observe.

174
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:50,160
- Observe?
- Observe the work in every department

175
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:53,400
If there's anything,
report to me in the office anytime.

176
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:55,360
- Okay?
- Understood.

177
00:23:16,480 --> 00:23:17,760
<i>The location info you filled in</i>

178
00:23:17,840 --> 00:23:20,400
<i>on your job application is being tracked</i>

179
00:23:21,120 --> 00:23:23,320
{\an8}<i>from a phone at Cosmic Central.</i>

180
00:24:12,440 --> 00:24:13,800
You're getting close to the target.

181
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:22,840
- Hey.
- Yes?

182
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:25,160
- Who's here? Come quick.
- Okay, let's go.

183
00:24:25,240 --> 00:24:26,760
- See who it is.
- Hurry!

184
00:24:34,160 --> 00:24:35,000
- Hello.
- Hello.

185
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:36,160
Hello.

186
00:24:36,920 --> 00:24:39,720
I'm Rin's friend from high school.

187
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:42,440
I heard she moved here. Is she home?

188
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:47,360
Or am I mistaken?

189
00:24:47,440 --> 00:24:50,480
No, no mistake.
Rin's back sometimes, right?

190
00:24:51,120 --> 00:24:54,520
Yes, but not often. She's busy with work.

191
00:24:54,600 --> 00:24:56,800
Do you have a message for her?

192
00:24:58,280 --> 00:25:01,040
Please tell Rin her friends miss her.

193
00:25:01,120 --> 00:25:02,080
Will do.

194
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:03,280
Thank you very much.

195
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:14,560
This is Rin's house.

196
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:38,000
"A young designer,
heir to the Kenji brand,

197
00:25:39,560 --> 00:25:43,240
keeps to himself,
doesn't like the spotlight."

198
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:51,280
What are you doing at 3C Group, Mr. Taiga?

199
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:02,640
Excuse me. Is Ms. Rin here?

200
00:26:02,720 --> 00:26:04,720
She's out.

201
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:06,000
Is she sick?

202
00:26:06,520 --> 00:26:09,200
She went to check the market.
Do you need to talk to her?

203
00:26:09,880 --> 00:26:12,080
I just wanted to ask a few questions.

204
00:26:12,160 --> 00:26:13,280
Please go ahead.

205
00:26:13,360 --> 00:26:15,400
We're ready to answer.

206
00:26:15,480 --> 00:26:17,400
No, that's okay. Thank you.

207
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:18,680
Yes.

208
00:26:31,520 --> 00:26:34,760
Mr. Taiga came. He really asked about you!

209
00:26:34,840 --> 00:26:37,640
Thanks! I'll bring some snacks later.

210
00:26:42,720 --> 00:26:45,520
If anyone asks,
just say what you said earlier.

211
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:47,280
Rin's gone to work.

212
00:26:47,360 --> 00:26:49,280
She doesn't come home often.

213
00:27:24,800 --> 00:27:26,400
What's stressing you out?

214
00:27:36,360 --> 00:27:38,240
If work's no fun,

215
00:27:39,840 --> 00:27:42,160
want to talk about something else?

216
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:46,560
Our promise.

217
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:51,880
Ugh!

218
00:29:23,080 --> 00:29:24,080
Ugh.

219
00:29:34,560 --> 00:29:36,000
Thank you

220
00:29:36,840 --> 00:29:38,040
for your courage,

221
00:29:39,600 --> 00:29:41,560
for helping a stranger like me.

222
00:30:10,400 --> 00:30:11,720
This wound

223
00:30:12,520 --> 00:30:14,200
made me realize

224
00:30:15,680 --> 00:30:17,640
who I love the most.

225
00:30:36,040 --> 00:30:40,000
Go to France and see my Daddy, okay?

226
00:30:44,520 --> 00:30:45,840
I can't go yet.

227
00:30:52,880 --> 00:30:54,120
Okay.

228
00:30:56,680 --> 00:30:59,720
If you want to deal
with the people who killed your father,

229
00:31:00,880 --> 00:31:03,200
I'll give you six more months.

230
00:31:04,560 --> 00:31:06,120
Once it's done,

231
00:31:07,360 --> 00:31:12,360
we'll get married right away,
with no excuses.

232
00:32:01,160 --> 00:32:03,400
I designed this suit for Mr. Naruban.

233
00:32:10,040 --> 00:32:11,120
Ms. Nun.

234
00:32:12,800 --> 00:32:14,480
- Ms. Nun.
- Yes?

235
00:32:14,560 --> 00:32:15,920
Do you like it?

236
00:32:16,600 --> 00:32:18,200
I like it!

237
00:32:18,280 --> 00:32:20,440
I'll call Dad right away.

238
00:32:38,560 --> 00:32:40,120
I'm not changing a thing.

239
00:32:40,200 --> 00:32:43,520
I'll wear my outfit as it is.
What's your problem, Nun?

240
00:32:43,600 --> 00:32:46,560
Do what I say.
If I didn't say it, don't do it.

241
00:32:56,960 --> 00:32:58,320
Well, my dad…

242
00:32:58,400 --> 00:33:00,360
Want me to try talking to Mr. Naruban?

243
00:33:01,600 --> 00:33:03,960
He might have a different perspective
on the clothes.

244
00:33:04,040 --> 00:33:07,200
If we talk, he might be more open.

245
00:33:08,960 --> 00:33:10,320
Okay.

246
00:33:10,400 --> 00:33:13,560
If my dad comes, I'll join in too.

247
00:34:03,400 --> 00:34:04,800
What's up? Why are you braking so often?

248
00:34:04,880 --> 00:34:06,600
Looks like someone's following us.

249
00:34:54,120 --> 00:34:55,639
The president is here.

250
00:35:12,440 --> 00:35:14,480
Thank you for working
so diligently for us.

251
00:35:18,840 --> 00:35:21,920
What information did you need, Dad?
Why not call me?

252
00:35:23,440 --> 00:35:26,880
Using a staff member at that level,
what would she know?

253
00:35:29,120 --> 00:35:31,520
I didn't call Rin to ask about the data.

254
00:35:33,440 --> 00:35:36,240
I asked her if she wants to do
another kind of work.

255
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:37,920
Work?

256
00:35:38,560 --> 00:35:39,800
Bodyguard.

257
00:35:42,400 --> 00:35:46,800
Dad, we have the money.
We can hire a professional anywhere!

258
00:35:46,880 --> 00:35:49,200
Do you know what I just encountered?

259
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:21,240
Are you okay, sir?

260
00:36:22,280 --> 00:36:23,280
I'm okay.

261
00:36:31,480 --> 00:36:34,040
What about the license plate
of the car that followed you?

262
00:36:34,120 --> 00:36:36,520
I checked with the deputy. It was fake.

263
00:36:42,040 --> 00:36:44,680
This isn't the first time
Rin risked her life to help me.

264
00:36:46,520 --> 00:36:50,560
I should promote and support those
who are brave and capable,

265
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:54,160
and not put them in a department
that doesn't suit them.

266
00:36:54,240 --> 00:36:56,240
The other staff must be confused

267
00:36:56,880 --> 00:36:58,640
about promotions here.

268
00:36:58,720 --> 00:37:00,280
As long as I'm not confused.

269
00:37:04,360 --> 00:37:05,320
Rin.

270
00:37:06,160 --> 00:37:07,400
Yes, sir.

271
00:37:08,160 --> 00:37:11,000
Go make a new key card
with access to all zones,

272
00:37:11,520 --> 00:37:13,920
and start assisting me from tomorrow.

273
00:37:14,680 --> 00:37:16,120
Yes, President.

274
00:37:38,400 --> 00:37:39,640
Excuse me.

275
00:37:56,520 --> 00:37:59,920
Quick reflexes, just like a bodyguard.

276
00:38:44,480 --> 00:38:45,960
<i>I messed up.</i>

277
00:38:46,040 --> 00:38:48,040
I thought following Naruban would be easy.

278
00:38:48,560 --> 00:38:51,920
It's even harder now.
Rin's now his bodyguard.

279
00:38:52,440 --> 00:38:53,680
Rin again?

280
00:39:19,840 --> 00:39:21,320
Stressed about work, dear?

281
00:39:25,120 --> 00:39:28,640
I want to get rid of one
of Dad's staff. I hate her.

282
00:39:29,400 --> 00:39:33,040
She's trying to stand out
to get his attention.

283
00:39:33,800 --> 00:39:35,200
And it's not just Dad.

284
00:39:35,280 --> 00:39:38,520
She flirts with Mr. Taiga too.
I don't want to lose.

285
00:39:38,600 --> 00:39:43,240
Hey, why are you comparing yourself
to someone at that level?

286
00:39:43,320 --> 00:39:46,240
Everyone's focused on Rin.
They give her too much credit.

287
00:39:46,960 --> 00:39:48,120
How about this?

288
00:39:48,200 --> 00:39:49,560
Let Mr. Taiga meet me.

289
00:39:50,200 --> 00:39:51,360
I can help figure out

290
00:39:51,440 --> 00:39:54,920
what will make him click with you more.

291
00:40:28,560 --> 00:40:30,960
Nothing can happen to Mr. Naruban, Rin.

292
00:40:31,040 --> 00:40:33,920
Fire Phoenix will make this world
completely equal.

293
00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:36,040
No more social inequality of any kind.

294
00:40:38,200 --> 00:40:41,680
And to do this, we'll need to use
everything he has,

295
00:40:42,840 --> 00:40:44,560
money and faith.

296
00:40:46,760 --> 00:40:50,160
We'll tear down the rotten structures
eating this country alive.

297
00:40:51,720 --> 00:40:53,560
No good cop should be bullied.

298
00:40:55,840 --> 00:40:57,720
No officer should die on duty,

299
00:40:58,880 --> 00:41:02,320
only to have a flag draped over their body
and a curse following them.

300
00:41:03,240 --> 00:41:06,680
No more good cops
dying dishonorably, like Phumin.

301
00:41:08,640 --> 00:41:10,680
Don't let anything slip by.

302
00:41:12,160 --> 00:41:15,880
Find out who's attacking

303
00:41:16,840 --> 00:41:18,440
and threatening Mr. Naruban.

304
00:41:46,120 --> 00:41:48,280
You said manipulating the price
would be easy!

305
00:41:48,360 --> 00:41:51,360
Why don't your followers
believe the rumors you spread?

306
00:41:51,440 --> 00:41:54,640
I think something's off.

307
00:41:54,720 --> 00:41:58,160
Someone must be acting as a major player
to crash the price this badly.

308
00:41:59,880 --> 00:42:02,200
Someone with enough money
to take us down like this.

309
00:42:17,480 --> 00:42:18,720
Who are you here to see?

310
00:42:18,800 --> 00:42:20,560
I'm here for Mr. Taiga.

311
00:42:39,280 --> 00:42:40,440
Tell him his fiancée is here.

312
00:43:17,200 --> 00:43:18,280
Dad.

313
00:43:19,440 --> 00:43:20,680
Don't worry.

314
00:43:20,760 --> 00:43:23,600
I'll launch a new platform to raise funds.

315
00:43:23,680 --> 00:43:25,840
Humans are greedy, Dad.

316
00:43:26,520 --> 00:43:30,080
If we hype it in the media
and promise good returns,

317
00:43:30,160 --> 00:43:32,960
even selling blank paper,
they'll give us money.

318
00:43:33,560 --> 00:43:37,600
The law has loopholes
that let us profit from their greed, Dad.

319
00:43:44,320 --> 00:43:47,200
Taiga, did you see the board this morning?

320
00:43:47,280 --> 00:43:50,480
Stocks and 3C-Coin got smashed.

321
00:43:51,480 --> 00:43:52,920
Do you know who did it?

322
00:43:56,960 --> 00:43:58,320
Ratee's father.

323
00:44:05,680 --> 00:44:08,360
{\an8}<i>With a pretty face and figure like yours,</i>

324
00:44:08,440 --> 00:44:11,120
{\an8}<i>you'd be better at something fun.</i>

325
00:44:12,600 --> 00:44:15,600
{\an8}Please me properly, and I'll promote you.

326
00:44:15,680 --> 00:44:19,000
{\an8}<i>Everything about Taiga, report only to me.</i>

327
00:44:19,080 --> 00:44:19,920
{\an8}Yes, sir.

328
00:44:55,200 --> 00:44:57,240
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn

